                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14327: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-25T21:00:00+03:25"
                            >August 25, 1941—9 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.</hi>]</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 25—4 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>104. The British note mentioned in my No. 103<note n="89" xml:id="d396fn89">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> and a similar note from the Russian Government were delivered to the
                    Prime Minister at 4 a.m. today. The hour of delivery was advanced in view of the
                    instructions of the Soviet Ambassador to deliver his note without delay.</p>
                <p>The Shah has asked to see the Russian and British Envoys at [apparent omission]
                    a.m. this morning. I shall report the results of their conversation immediately
                    thereafter.</p>
                <p>All is quiet in Tehran this morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
